  <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">About this service</p>
      <h2>The W1 is a reference washer. Service has to be reference-level too.</h2>
      <p>The Miele W1 is the European compact washer that doesn't compromise on capacity or build quality to fit 24-inch installations. The Honeycomb drum has 7,000 microscopic cavities that form a water film between fabric and stainless steel, reducing mechanical wear on delicate items. The direct-drive motor is rated for 10,000 operating hours — Miele tests each motor through a 20-year duty cycle before signing off on the platform. TwinDos dispenses precisely the right amount of UltraPhase 1 (main wash) and UltraPhase 2 (color protection) detergent for each cycle, no measuring and no overdose risk. CapDosing handles specialty detergents (delicates, wool, sports) via dissolvable capsules. HomeCare 2.0 is the internal architecture — lifetime-sealed bearings, reinforced suspension, hardened drum cross to survive two decades of service.</p>
      <p>Most of our W1 calls are generations 2021-2023 — the wave of W1 owners whose 2-year Miele USA warranty has just closed and who are starting to see first service needs. Typical failures at year 3-5 are: drain filter clogs (free cleanup), shock absorber early wear on units with aggressive spin use, door lock motor intermittent, TwinDos sensor drift. None of these are major repairs — W1 is a long-life platform, and service at the 3-7 year mark is maintenance-level work that adds another decade of life.</p>
      <p>Most W1 installs in LA are in condominiums along the Wilshire Corridor, Century City, West Hollywood high-rises, and townhouses in Brentwood, Bel Air, and Pacific Palisades — spaces where the 24-inch format was specified because 27-inch American laundry wouldn't fit. The demographic is specific: owners who chose Miele for reasons that matter over 15-year ownership, not first-cost shoppers. That shapes our service approach — we diagnose carefully, carry genuine Miele parts, and explain the repair economics honestly.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

