  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Miele W1 washer repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>My W1 is 24 inches — does format matter?</summary>
        <p>Yes. 24-inch European compact — not 27-inch American standard. Parts are Miele-specific (generic won't fit), diagnostic protocols differ, technician needs W1 training. We stock W1 parts on the truck and our techs are trained on the platform.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F11 — drain fault</summary>
        <p>Open drain filter hatch at front-bottom-left, clear debris (coins, hairpins typical). 60% resolve at filter free. If persistent: drain pump impeller or motor ($285-$385). LA hard water accelerates pump wear on 7+ year units.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F211-F214 — TwinDos error</summary>
        <p>Sensor fault in dosing system. Workaround: dose manually via top drawer. Diagnostic: reseat flacons (20% resolve), TwinDos Care rinse ($95), sensor replacement ($185-$265). Preventive: run TwinDos Care every 6 months on idle W1.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>W1 bangs during spin</summary>
        <p>Shock absorber wear (year 7-10). Replace set of 4 for balanced damping ($385-$540). We check springs and drum mounts at same visit — sometimes appears as shock wear but is broken spring mount.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Door won't unlock</summary>
        <p>Clear drain filter first (residual water blocks unlock). If that fails, door lock motor ($195-$285). Emergency release behind filter hatch — we show location. Don't force door — turns $195 into $385.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Foam overload F16/F63</summary>
        <p>Wrong detergent. W1 needs ~1/3 the dose of a 27-inch American washer. Switch to Miele UltraPhase or low-foam HE detergent at reduced dose. Run rinse to clear. Persistent F16 = foam sensor drift ($165).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Miele washer repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: drain pump $285-$385, shock set $385-$540, door lock $195-$285, heating element $265-$385, control board $640-$920. Full pricing table above.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
